[1
Date: 29 Oct 2001
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Orlando Sentinel, Fri 26 Oct 2001 [edited

Dengue Fever Epidemic in Martinique
-----------------------------------
Dengue fever has killed an 81-year-old man in Martinique, where officials
think the mosquito-borne disease may reach epidemic proportions. The man,
whose identity was not released, died last week in northern Le Morne Rouge,
the Health and Social Development Directorate said on Wed 23 Oct 2001, Last
week, 380 new cases with symptoms of dengue were reported, and those people
are undergoing tests.
--
Pablo Nart
<p.nart@virgin.net>
