[2
Date: 30 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency (via COMTEX), Tue 30 Oct 2001 [edited

Dengue Fever Claims 60 Lives in Vietnam
---------------------------------------
HANOI: At least 60 people have died of dengue fever in Vietnam so far this
year, or 17 more deaths than last year, as the disease swept through a vast
region in the country.
As many as 30 198 cases of dengue fever have been registered in Vietnam to
date, a year-on-year rise of 69.2 percent, the Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported on Tue 30 Oct. In October alone, dengue fever has spread to over
29 cities and provinces with 2408 people suffering from the disease. Most
of these cases were found in the Mekong delta, which has been worst hit by
seasonal flooding.
The last [outbreak of this contagious disease in Vietnam occurred in 1998
[affecting 234 920 people with 377 deaths.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
